<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">solastra</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Im trying to find out any info on the mark of retrobution 54th level cleric spell.<BR>I am a bit confused on how it works an who you cast it on.  Anyone have experience with this certain spell?<BR>Thanks for any info. <BR>Solastra </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You cast it on mobs like MoK.  Whenever that mob hits someone while under the effect of this spell, they take 15 pts of damage.  It's a damage shield cast on the mob instead of the players.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Borundin</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Its a very nice spell that I bought recently! Spell works just like Gello explained. I've been using it to powerlevel another char and it is even possible to powerlevel a character on the SAME account. Here is the trick: Root a mob, preferably long duration. Mark it with Retribution. Log off your cleric and log on your twinked melee and let the mob kill itself on you. Much trouble for not very good exp but still its doable at lower levels =)<BR>I have also landed this on alot of mobs in ToV HoT and it seems to stick on most after a couple of recasts (Im only lvl 56).<P><BR><P>------------------<BR>Borundin Tjurnacke 56 Cleric &lt;Immortal Spirits&gt;<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aanar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When I need to kill a greenie, it's quite useful also.  Depending on the mob and your AC, it takes less mana to MoR, melee, and heal yourself than to do the standard root 'n' nuke.<P>I soloed in lower guk doing this to pick up some azure sleeves.  Oh three minos on me?  Np, MoR each one, swing away, and root the last one as it tries to run away.  Patch myself up with a CE, med for a bit, and  I'm good to go again.<P>With more practic, maybe I can be a proffesional farmer.  Rofl.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gryfalia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Actually if you can 2-Box it is kinda sick for PLing.  I have a 25 Ranger twink (well, was 23 when I started this) sitting in Tenebrous Mountains and I buff him with out group buffs and CSoW.  I then pull an alien or Wolf to him (not bats, hard to root them).  Root it, MoR and MoK it, sit down and let the beating commence.  Battles last 2 minutes tops and he gains between 1.5 and 2 blues per kill.  23 was over stupid fast.<P>Not only that, but his combat stats max out in a matter of minutes.  And these critters will be red for another 10 levels!  Holy smokes!  MoR rules..;-)<P>Gryfalia<BR>58 Templar of Brell<BR>Imperial Guards<BR>Druzzil Ro</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
